405
00:34:07,170 --> 00:34:10,130
- Take a photo for us. 
 - Take our picture.

406
00:34:21,130 --> 00:34:22,770
- What's next?
- Your call.

407
00:34:22,770 --> 00:34:25,490
Haunted house.

408
00:34:25,490 --> 00:34:29,270
I'm too young to keep up.
Go ahead. I'll just chill here.

409
00:34:29,270 --> 00:34:35,190
Chen Jia Yu, this is an amusement park.

410
00:34:35,190 --> 00:34:37,890
He's scared of ghosts?

411
00:34:37,890 --> 00:34:41,090
Are you afraid of ghosts?

412
00:34:41,090 --> 00:34:45,970
Nonsense. Take care of my childish godmother.

413
00:34:45,970 --> 00:34:50,350
I recommend the Ferris wheel.
It's more romantic and private.

414
00:34:50,350 --> 00:34:53,490
I won't third-wheel you guys anymore.

415
00:34:53,490 --> 00:34:57,890
Oh, call me if you need photos taken.

416
00:34:59,890 --> 00:35:03,630
Ya En must figure out
what books this kid's been reading.

417
00:35:03,630 --> 00:35:05,410
I can hear you.

418
00:35:05,410 --> 00:35:08,830
Fine. Wait there. We'll be right back.

419
00:35:08,830 --> 00:35:09,990
Go ahead.

420
00:35:09,990 --> 00:35:11,690
Bye.

421
00:35:12,570 --> 00:35:14,910
- Let's go. 
 - Where are you going?

422
00:35:14,910 --> 00:35:17,830
- You think it's a real date? 
 - Isn't it?

423
00:35:17,830 --> 00:35:22,950
What about the kid?
I won't let you take care of our baby.

424
00:35:22,950 --> 00:35:24,490
Let's get some water.

425
00:35:24,490 --> 00:35:26,090
Okay.

426
00:35:27,990 --> 00:35:31,790
Wang Si Si? It really is you.

427
00:35:32,970 --> 00:35:36,730
Why are you alone at the amusement park?

428
00:35:36,730 --> 00:35:39,870
I'm here for fun. What about you?

429
00:35:39,870 --> 00:35:43,830
Me? I was dragged here against my will.

430
00:35:47,350 --> 00:35:52,190
Wang Si Si, why did you
glue teardrops on your mask?

431
00:35:52,190 --> 00:35:57,230
Because I feel like the Little Mermaid.
She lives underwater.

432
00:35:57,230 --> 00:36:00,790
But people see her tears when she's on land.

433
00:36:00,790 --> 00:36:04,410
School's starting soon. I hate school.

434
00:36:04,410 --> 00:36:07,530
I don't like people seeing my tears.

435
00:36:08,510 --> 00:36:11,010
Have you told your parents and teachers?

436
00:36:11,010 --> 00:36:16,050
I told Mom, but she's too busy making money

437
00:36:16,050 --> 00:36:20,350
for my little brother to care about me.

438
00:36:20,350 --> 00:36:25,590
I'm scared she will scold me and stop loving me.

439
00:36:25,590 --> 00:36:28,870
So I stopped talking about it.

440
00:36:31,350 --> 00:36:34,790
No way. Your mom definitely loves you.

441
00:36:34,790 --> 00:36:37,250
It's you. Grim Reaper.

442
00:36:37,250 --> 00:36:41,570
Did you tell your mom why you hate school?

443
00:36:42,450 --> 00:36:48,790
Every time I try, she yells at me.

444
00:36:48,790 --> 00:36:50,890
That makes me even sadder.

445
00:36:50,890 --> 00:36:54,070
Grim Reaper, do you have any candy?

446
00:36:54,070 --> 00:36:58,810
Can we still play the guessing game
with candy in pockets?

447
00:36:58,810 --> 00:37:04,050
Let's play a different game today.
We have other friends here.

448
00:37:04,050 --> 00:37:05,750
Alright.

449
00:37:06,770 --> 00:37:09,790
I think your mask design is great.

450
00:37:09,790 --> 00:37:13,430
Keep wearing it all the way home.

451
00:37:13,430 --> 00:37:16,450
Your mom will notice it when you get home.

452
00:37:16,450 --> 00:37:19,790
Then you can tell her why you made it this way.

453
00:37:19,790 --> 00:37:24,090
But wearing a mask is weird. People will stare.

454
00:37:24,090 --> 00:37:28,050
Don't worry. We'll join you and wear masks.

455
00:37:28,050 --> 00:37:30,990
With the mask on,
you can make any expression you want.

456
00:37:30,990 --> 00:37:33,870
Feel free to cry and laugh.

457
00:37:35,430 --> 00:37:38,350
Whoever removes their mask gets eliminated.

458
00:37:38,350 --> 00:37:40,710
It's a competition.

459
00:37:41,310 --> 00:37:43,090
Come on.

460
00:37:43,090 --> 00:37:46,210
This is for you. Grab one for me.

461
00:37:50,010 --> 00:37:53,670
What color do you want? What're you making now?

462
00:38:00,370 --> 00:38:01,930
Si Si, are you tired?

463
00:38:01,930 --> 00:38:03,630
No.

464
00:38:05,150 --> 00:38:08,990
Thank you for looking after my daughter.

465
00:38:08,990 --> 00:38:13,390
How could you run off without telling me?
I've been searching everywhere.

466
00:38:13,390 --> 00:38:16,430
It's okay. Si Si is a good girl.

467
00:38:16,430 --> 00:38:21,750
Si Si, don't forget
what you wanted to tell your mom.

468
00:38:21,750 --> 00:38:23,090
Bye, big brother and sister.

469
00:38:23,090 --> 00:38:26,830
- Bye.
- Bye.

470
00:38:29,450 --> 00:38:31,930
Is Si Si...

471
00:38:31,930 --> 00:38:35,090
Kids can be very sentimental.

472
00:38:35,090 --> 00:38:40,730
If their parents could notice the problem,
the kids would be better soon.

473
00:38:41,450 --> 00:38:47,150
I regret it. I should've
painted mine as a clown like you did.

474
00:38:47,150 --> 00:38:51,030
Yours looks nice. It's like a sunny day.

475
00:38:54,010 --> 00:39:01,230
You know what? You're even better than I imagined.

476
00:39:01,230 --> 00:39:02,670
Really?

477
00:39:02,670 --> 00:39:04,470
Yeah.

478
00:39:06,090 --> 00:39:08,210
